    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-01-15T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-01-15T23:00:00-05:00" n="477"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d477">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.116/122: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-01-16T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 16, 1934—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received January 16—7:42
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>39. Legation’s 5, January 3, 3 p.m.<note n="21" xml:id="d477fn21">
                        <ref target="frus1933v03#pg_593">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 593</ref>.</note> Following from
                    American Consul General at Canton to the Legation and Nanking: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“January 15, 5 p.m. Inspector General of Foreign Affairs informed British
                            Consul General and myself today that foreign oil companies are on the
                            same basis as native companies in respect to deferred payment tax plan,
                            but that native distillers are now granted subsidy from the provincial
                            treasury. Inspector General said that he had been promised a letter on
                            these points from the Commissioner of Finance and upon its receipt he
                            would confirm these statements to us in writing and also set forth the
                            channel on which the subsidy is granted.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>The Legation is taking no action in the matter pending receipt of information as
                    to the nature of subsidy proposed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
